Looking at the proof goal, I need to show that `Pr[=x | $[0..n]] = Pr[=y | $[0..n]]` for any `x y : ZMod (n + 1)`.

The key insight is that `$[0..n]` produces a uniform distribution over `Fin (n + 1)`, and `ZMod (n + 1)` is equivalent to `Fin (n + 1)`. The probability of selecting any specific element from a uniform distribution is the same.

Looking at similar instances in the code, particularly the `Fin (n + 1)` instance which has the same structure, I can see that `probOutput_uniformFin` should give us what we need - the probability is uniform for all elements.

